cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a neural architecture search algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the incorporation of structural information in the architecture, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep learning for person re-identification could also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
